    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-06T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-06T20:00:00-05:00" n="709"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d709">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/8817: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-06T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 6, 1943—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4104. Your 4393, 5th.<note n="71" xml:id="d709fn71">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Recognizing the importance of winding up the negotiations as soon as possible and
                    as you have already received our views and desiderata on all important points
                    covered by the negotiations, we think it now <pb facs="0797" n="785"
                        xml:id="pg_785"/> feasible to authorize you to agree without further
                    reference to us to such further modifications in the proposed agreement as you
                    deem reasonable and which do not materially modify any principles already agreed
                    upon. This authority is given to avoid unnecessary delay in concluding the
                    agreement.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Stockholm as Department’s no. 755.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
